content.text:
Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. The RichTextEditor uses `color="var(--accent-purple)"` for its BarLoader -- that is the established pattern. The `--loader-color` variable is also available (set to `#C4943E` in light mode and `#D4A853` in dark mode). Let me now produce the complete implementation plan.

---

## Detailed Implementation Plan: ProfilePage Editor UI Enhancement

This plan is organized into 6 files, addressed in dependency order. Each section contains the exact changes needed, why they are needed, and the specific code to write.

---

### Phase 1: Bug Fixes (highest priority, foundational)

---

#### FILE 1: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\ProfilePage\MyProfile.jsx`

This file contains 5 of the 9 bugs and is the parent orchestrator for all profile editing state.

**Change 1 -- Fix typo `opendRichTextEditor` (Bug #3)**

On line 85, rename the function from `opendRichTextEditor` to `openRichTextEditor`. Also update the reference on line 389 where it is passed to `<WriteJournalButton onOpen={opendRichTextEditor} />`.

```jsx
// Line 85: Before
const opendRichTextEditor = () => {
    setShowEditor(true);
};

// Line 85: After
const openRichTextEditor = () => {
    setShowEditor(true);
};

// Line 389: Before
<WriteJournalButton onOpen={opendRichTextEditor} />

// Line 389: After
<WriteJournalButton onOpen={openRichTextEditor} />
```

**Change 2 -- Fix typo `hancleClickCancelFontSelect` (Bug #2)**

On line 287, rename from `hancleClickCancelFontSelect` to `handleClickCancelFontSelect`. Also update the reference on line 310 where it is passed as a prop.

```jsx
// Line 287: Before
const hancleClickCancelFontSelect = () => {

// Line 287: After
const handleClickCancelFontSelect = () => {

// Line 310: Before
hancleClickCancelFontSelect={hancleClickCancelFontSelect}

// Line 310: After
handleClickCancelFontSelect={handleClickCancelFontSelect}
```

**Change 3 -- Fix cancel resetting font color to empty string (Bug #9)**

On line 289 inside the cancel handler, instead of `setFontColor("")`, revert to the last saved value from `userData`.

```jsx
// Line 287-290: Before
const hancleClickCancelFontSelect = () => {
    setShowFontColorSelector(false);
    setFontColor("");
};

// After
const handleClickCancelFontSelect = () => {
    setShowFontColorSelector(false);
    setFontColor(userData?.profile_font_color || "");
};
```

**Change 4 -- Remove duplicate `setProfileEditAvatar(file)` (Bug #5)**

On lines 121 and 123, the same call appears twice. Remove line 121.

```jsx
// Lines 119-133: Before
const handleImageOnChange = (e) => {
    const file = e.target.files[0];
    setProfileEditAvatar(file);
    if (file) {
        setProfileEditAvatar(file);
        // ...

// After
const handleImageOnChange = (e) => {
    const file = e.target.files[0];
    if (file) {
        setProfileEditAvatar(file);
        // ...
    } else {
        setProfileEditAvatar(null);
        setEditImagePreview("");
    }
};
```

Note: Also moved `setProfileEditAvatar(null)` into the else branch for clarity, since when no file is selected, the avatar should be null.

**Change 5 -- Add error state and user-visible error feedback (Bug #8)**

Add a new state variable for error messages. Modify all three save handlers to set a visible error message instead of silently throwing. Add an auto-clearing timeout.

```jsx
// After line 60 (existing state declarations), add:
const [saveError, setSaveError] = useState("");

// Add a helper to show and auto-clear errors:
const showError = useCallback((message) => {
    setSaveError(message);
    setTimeout(() => setSaveError(""), 4000);
}, []);
```

Then modify the three save handlers:

For `handleSaveProfileEdit` (line 155):
```jsx
// Line 181: Before
} catch {
    throw new Error("error saving update");
} finally {

// After
} catch {
    showError("Failed to save profile. Please try again.");
    return;
